fields.summary: Endpoint to provide live documentation for Centralway

issuetype.description: A big user story that needs to be broken down.
issuetype.name: Epic

fields.description:
Related to https://centralway.atlassian.net/wiki/display/TECH/Technology+Projects+Quality

The goal of the endpoint is to be the “Core” for documentation. This endpoint can be queried in a way that can be used then within confluence, for instance http://documentation.centralway.com/m-ios-api/last-updated should return the last time the project “m-ios-api” was updated. It would return a small html object (thus HTML include macro) with the last time the project was updated.

The same way we have a Core that handles all the banking information, we could have a “Core” for documentation. Not part of this first step, but if we then can process how this documentation endpoint is processed, we can have more information about the internals of Centralway in terms of document management.
